sDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5754022\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5754022\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104inu1704706908242.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/inu1704706908242.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/inu1704706908242.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"sjo1665702842251\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Field Widgets\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Most widgets are field-level widgets that represent scalar data values. If no widget\n      is explicitly selected, the default widget is used—it represents the field as a single line\n      edit box.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__p_d11603e1_d11604e1_d11605e1\">You can set widget properties for all field widgets in Properties Inspector. For field widgets in forms and dynamic server pages, you can also set them in the initialization file and in script. it is not possible to do this for field widgets in static server pages.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__p_d11606e1_d11607e1_d11608e1\">In ProcScript, you can use:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__li_d5375e1_d5376e1_d5377e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zie1665702558978.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zie1665702558978.html\" title=\"Return or set the current widget properties of a field.\">$properties</a> to set the default\n            widget properties</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__li_d5378e1_d5379e1_d5380e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aud1705998763272.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aud1705998763272.html\" title=\"Return or set the current widget properties of an instance of a field.\">$fieldproperties</a> to set the widget\n            properties of a specific field instance.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__li_d5381e1_d5382e1_d5383e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hqv1665702558806.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hqv1665702558806.html\" title=\"Return or set the position and size for a specific instance of a field widget in a Form.\">$paintedfieldproperties</a> to dynamically change the size and position of the widget.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__note_w14ab1b5b7_w15ab1b5_w16ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Although the Widget Properties dialog\n         of some widgets (such as list and spinner widgets) enables you to define the ValRep\n         property, this is a field-level property and can be set with <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"akv1665702559054.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/akv1665702559054.html\" title=\"Return or set the ValRep used by a widget for a field.\">$valrep</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hxn1665702558407.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hxn1665702558407.html\" title=\"Return or set the associative (ValRep) list for an instance of a field.\">$fieldvalrep</a>.</div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__section_dcz_xnn_11c\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d862457e103\">Field Widgets for Forms and Reports</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__p_d11612e1_d11613e1_d11614e1\">Form components support a wide range of widgets.\n            Report components support only non-editable EditBox and Picture widgets. For more\n            information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zck1665702627225.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zck1665702627225.html\" title=\"Widgets in Form components determine the appearance and behavior of fields, labels, occurrences, and entities displayed in components running on Windows.\">Widgets for Forms and Reports</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__p_d11615e1_d11616e1_d11617e1\">In character mode applications, widgets are not\n            supported. In this case, <dfn class=\"term\">Unifields</dfn> are used. These are field\n            representations that can handle all data types and work identically in both GUI\n            (Windows) and character mode. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wxx1665702627294.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wxx1665702627294.html\" title=\"Unifields are field representations for displaying and entering data in character mode. They also work in Windows, but support only basic video attributes (bright, underline, inverse, and blink). They do not support proportional fonts or other properties.\">Unifields</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__section_o5t_znn_11c\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d862457e133\">Field Widgets for Dynamic Server Pages</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__p_d11621e1_d11622e1_d11623e1\">Field widgets for dynamic server pages are styled\n            using properties that map to HTML attributes. They can be set in ProcScript, but it is\n            more common to use JavaScript to reduce the need to get updates from the server. For\n            more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sno1665702583691.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sno1665702583691.html\" title=\"Widget definitions for Dynamic Server Pages (DSPs) are used to generate the HTML elements and controls used to represent fields, labels, occurrences, and entities displayed in the client browser.\">Widgets for Dynamic Server Pages</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__p_d11624e1_d11625e1_d11626e1\">For field widgets in dynamic server pages, you can\n            also use the following JavaScript APIs to set widget properties in the browser:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">JavaScript API Functions for Widget Properties</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1__entry__1\">Member</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1__entry__2\"> Purpose </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fql1665702536920.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fql1665702536920.html\" title=\"Restores the initial widget properties of the Uniface data object.\">clearProperties()</a>\n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1__entry__2\"> Restores the initial widget \t\t\t properties of the object.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pym1665702536682.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pym1665702536682.html\" title=\"Restores the initial value of the specified property.\">clearProperty()</a>\n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1__entry__2\"> Restores the initial value of the\n\t\t\t\t specified widget property.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"med1665702536765.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/med1665702536765.html\" title=\"Returns the properties of this Uniface data object.\">getProperties()</a>\n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1__entry__2\"> Returns the widget properties of the object</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hwh1665702536527.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hwh1665702536527.html\" title=\"Returns the value of a property of this Uniface data object.\">getProperty()</a>\n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1__entry__2\"> Returns the value of a widget property of the\n\t\t\t\t object</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qbz1665702536840.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qbz1665702536840.html\" title=\"Sets widget properties for a Uniface data object in JavaScript.\">setProperties()</a>\n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1__entry__2\">Sets one or more widget properties for the\n object. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nkl1665702536608.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nkl1665702536608.html\" title=\"Sets the specified widget property to a given value.\">setProperty()</a>\n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sjo1665702842251__table_d1202e1_d1203e1_d1204e1__entry__2\">Sets the specified widget property for the\n object to a given value.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sjo1665702842251__section_ep4_d4n_11c\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d862457e313\">Field Widgets for Static Server Pages</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">These widgets are implemented as XHTML controls, and they do not support logical\n            widgets. To set their properties, you can edit the server page layout. For more\n            information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yjb1665702863271.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yjb1665702863271.html\" title=\"Widgets for static server pages (USPs) are HTML controls that determine how data is represented in the web page.\">Widgets for Static Server Pages</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xxb1719471602895.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xxb1719471602895.html\" title=\"The webgen command generates the XHTML document that is displayed in the browser in response to request for a static server page. You can influence the XHTML that it generates by manually editing the server page layout.\">Customizing the XHTML Generated for USPs</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qxh1718771608803.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Widget Reference: Dynamic Server Pages</a><p>Widgets in dynamic server pages (DSPs) determine the appearance and behavior of fields, labels, occurrences, and entities displayed in the client browser.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lov1718340866615.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Widget Reference: Forms and Reports</a><p>Widgets in Form components determine the appearance and behavior of fields, labels, occurrences, and entities in components running on Windows.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5754022\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5754022\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Field Widgets Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Field Widgets Most widgets are field-level widgets that represent scalar data values. If no widget is explicitly selected, the default widget is used—it represents the field as a single line edit box. You can set widget properties for all field widgets in Properties Inspector. For field widgets in forms and dynamic server pages, you can also set them in the initialization file and in script. it is not possible to do this for field widgets in static server pages. In ProcScript, you can use: $properties to set the default widget properties $fieldproperties to set the widget properties of a specific field instance. $paintedfieldproperties to dynamically change the size and position of the widget. Note: Although the Widget Properties dialog of some widgets (such as list and spinner widgets) enables you to define the ValRep property, this is a field-level property and can be set with $valrep and $fieldvalrep . Field Widgets for Forms and Reports Form components support a wide range of widgets. Report components support only non-editable EditBox and Picture widgets. For more information, see Widgets for Forms and Reports . In character mode applications, widgets are not supported. In this case, Unifields are used. These are field representations that can handle all data types and work identically in both GUI (Windows) and character mode. For more information, see Unifields . Field Widgets for Dynamic Server Pages Field widgets for dynamic server pages are styled using properties that map to HTML attributes. They can be set in ProcScript, but it is more common to use JavaScript to reduce the need to get updates from the server. For more information, see Widgets for Dynamic Server Pages . For field widgets in dynamic server pages, you can also use the following JavaScript APIs to set widget properties in the browser: Table 1. JavaScript API Functions for Widget Properties Member Purpose clearProperties() Restores the initial widget properties of the object. clearProperty() Restores the initial value of the specified widget property. getProperties() Returns the widget properties of the object getProperty() Returns the value of a widget property of the object setProperties() Sets one or more widget properties for the object. setProperty() Sets the specified widget property for the object to a given value. Field Widgets for Static Server Pages These widgets are implemented as XHTML controls, and they do not support logical widgets. To set their properties, you can edit the server page layout. For more information, see Widgets for Static Server Pages and Customizing the XHTML Generated for USPs . Related Links Widget Reference: Dynamic Server Pages Widgets in dynamic server pages (DSPs) determine the appearance and behavior of fields, labels, occurrences, and entities displayed in the client browser. Widget Reference: Forms and Reports Widgets in Form components determine the appearance and behavior of fields, labels, occurrences, and entities in components running on Windows. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}